Brazil Coffee Output to Drop to 43.5 Million Bags This Year

-- B y   K a t i a   C o r t e s
-- 
2011-05-10T12:00:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/brazil-coffee-output-to-drop-to-43-5-million-bags-this-year.html
Coffee production in  Brazil , the
world’s biggest grower and exporter, will drop to 43.5 million
bags this year, down from 48.1 million bags last year, the
 Agriculture Ministry ’s crop-forecasting agency, known as Conab,
said today in an e-mailed report.  Conab said on Jan. 6 coffee growers would harvest between
41.9 million bags and 44.7 million bags this year.  One bag of coffee weighs 60 kilograms (132 pounds).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Cortes in Brasilia at  at
 kcortes@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net  